China’s railways transported 330 millions tons of cargo in April, growing 10.1% year on year, according to data released by the China Railway on Sunday. Green channels were opened for the transportation of essential goods like supplies for anti-epidemic fighting and agriculture, as well as thermal-coal. In April, China’s railways transported 6.03 million tons of agricultural supplies including fertilizer, pesticides and seeds, growing 47.6% year on year. And a total of 110 million tons of thermal coal was transported, up 12.1% on a yearly basis. Following strict epidemic control and prevention measures, the railway departments also strengthened cooperation with the international railways to improve the handling capacity of railway ports in China. In April, railway lines of the new western land-sea corridor transported 63,000 TEUs, growing 19.6% year on year. The China-Laos Railway handled 132,000 tons of goods, up 10% from the previous month. China-Europe freight train continued to operate steadily.